meta:Metadata.meta:Abstract: AFRL/RW tasked IAC MAC to develop Objectives and Key Results (OKRs) in support of Strategic Development Planning Process (SDPP) priorities and adopted concepts. IAC MAC personnel collaborated closely with AFRL/RW personnel and stakeholders to observe business practices and develop OKRs and recommend communications for the workforce (WF). To ensure AFRL/RW effectively executes the SDPP and ultimately support the organizations strategic end state in the development of lethal munitions Science and Technology (S and T) projects, a planning framework to identify SDPP goals and how AFRL/RW plans to achieve them was created. OKRs provide such a function by ensuring there is focus, alignment, and accountability towards an organizations goals. An objective is what an organization plans to achieve, while associated key results describe how an organization plans to achieve an objective. Focus aids the organization by providing what matters most to ensure the WF are working towards the same goal. Alignment is important as it communicates priorities across the organization, resulting in the WF understanding what they need to contribute to achieve the goal. OKRs also provide accountability and promote a deliberate dialogue within the WF on what can be accomplished and by whom. Lastly, clearly defined initiatives and tasks, are the specific projects and work efforts that must be accomplished to achieve desired results. This product provides a phased approach, with associated OKRs for each phase, to ensure the goals of the current SDPP are met. The OKRs define responsibilities driving S and T research to best meet warfighter needs. If implemented, OKRs will also lay the foundation for supporting initiatives and tasks and support client decision making for preparing the baseline of the 2024 SDPP cycle.
